text: Stood in line this morning for take away.  Line was really long (Saturday morning so it is expected) but couldn't wait for my sourdough toast lol!  As always, the strawberry peppercorn jam is just amazing!  Ordered also a breakfast sandwich on brioche, french toast, avocado toast with a 7 minute egg ($3 extra), an olive loaf, and a pomegranite iced tea.  I would have given this a 4 but the wait was ridiculous after ordering.  The people behind me in line were waiting for 4 coffees for over 20 minutes and my food took 1/2 hour.  With nowhere to sit, only a place to stand by the dirty dish drop off, 1/2 hour is an eternity.  Got home and no egg on the avocado toast to boot.  The brioche sandwich is a bit bland... I only ate 1/2 of it and left the rest on the counter for anyone else to eat and it is still there lol.  My son LOVED the French toast and my daughter said the avo toast was good.  Bummed about the egg though.  Will try again and hopefully it will be not so long... the kids in the kitchen area have no sense of urgency lol but again, good.  (Also, the guy taking the orders was SUPER sweet!)

text: This place !! From the moment I walked in the vibe was different . The receptionist listened and was friendly. Have you ever walked into a tattoo place they're kinda snobby you show them your idea and they snub you off ? I went to 805 tattoo and that was that . I live in Sacramento I was coming to visit . I had tried three whole tattoo places which refused and didn't even work with me to add this on a previous tattoo for me. Golden eagle takes walk in I was there around 12. Two hours later they called me. I had just gotten food but sprinted over immediately. Justin !! He is extremely detailed and takes pride in what he does. 4 hours later right before closing time he was done . He was shooting ideas off with me at first he didn't just turn me down. He was willing to work with me and even got it stenciled . His stencils were so amazing . Like I said he really takes pride and has been tattoo for years. He's really focused and this was his last day before a day off . Look at the details !!! Trust me you want this place . I stayed there four hours and all tattoo artists were so amazing positive and taking pride in the workplace and their work!! I love this place - I honestly thought about getting another tattoo done on my second day here . This is the most detailed tattoo I've ever gotten and to think the main purpose was just a cover up. I'm so happy with it !

categories: Food, Specialty Food, Nightlife, Restaurants, Local Flavor, Ethnic Food, Beer, Wine & Spirits, Bars, Mexican
text:
Fantastic food & exceptional service!

Owner Gabe really hooked it up. He shaped the perfect takeout menu for our group of 11 women, and everyone praised how absolutely bomb the food was.

I wish I had a 'before' pic of our wonderful spread--shredded chicken, carne asada, sautéed veggies, rice, mix of tortillas, onion & cilantro, chips, salsa, guac--but everyone seriously dove in and devoured the deliciousness!

And that guac, oh my - get two quarts of it!

There's so many Mexican food options in Santa Barbara, but Gabe really makes the takeout experience so effortless. He's super patient & unfailingly helpful, and the professionalism of Mex Authentic makes it the best spot for Mexican food in the area.

categories: Breakfast & Brunch, Coffee & Tea, Bakeries, Desserts, Donuts, Food, Restaurants
text:
I came super early on a Friday morning hoping to beat the rush (I literally got there 8:02) and there was already a line!! This place is small and the store itself also has Buena Onda so hook and press is near the middle/back.

They have a beautiful display of donuts and some of the flavors rotate in and out. I got 6 donuts (the blueberry pancake, the coastal fog, browned butter, the apple fritter, the lemon lavender, and the everything bagel) I wanted to try a bunch of flavors so I got a box and split with friends

Lemon Lavender: (4/5) I was really excited for this one which is a new flavor. It was a tad too sweet for me but the lavender flavor really shined through and its topped with little bits of lavender. There's a slight lemon aftertaste as well thats not too strong

Blueberry Pancake: (5/5) This one might be my favorite! It really tasted like a pancake and I loved the blueberry icing. It  was also quite sweet so I could only eat a little at a time but I kept wanting more!! 

Apple Fritter: (5/5) This apple fritter is only available on Fridays and I wish that wasn't the case because it is so DELISH. It seems simple but the texture and the bits of apple are sooo yummy. 

Everything Bagel: (4/5) I don't know why but I thought this one would be sweet...well it's not! It's a bit salty with cream cheese inside and I enjoyed it as a reprieve from all the sugar

Coastal Fog: (5/5) I forget what flavor this really is but it's delicious! (maybe a tea of some sort?) and it has a scrumptious whipped cream on top

Browned butter: (3.5/5) a bit too sweet for my liking and reminded me a bit of a cookie. You can really taste the brown butter flavor though.

The service was really friendly but not the fastest. I would love if they had a sampler so I could try them all but not buy an entire donut HAHA oh well...guess I'll just have to but the entire thing

text:
If you like spicy Japanese mayonnaise, which I do, then Edomasa is a good choice. All their spicy rolls have the spicy mayonnaise, and it's awesome. 

I like edomasa because they have a huge menu with a lot of different choices, and everything is pretty tasty. I've never had something there that I didn't enjoy. I especially like the basic rolls there such as spicy tuna and spicy california rolls (gotta have that mayo)! Their agedashi tofu is also really good. 

And save room for the red bean ice cream...mmmmm. 

I'm giving them 4 stars only because it's not the best sushi I've ever had - but it's really good. They also don't have a true "crunchy roll."

categories: Shopping, Herbs & Spices, Nurseries & Gardening, Specialty Food, Home & Garden, Food
text: My friend and I spend a lot of time gardening, spend a lot of time in nurseries, and know what to look for and feel we know what should be paid for it, as we both have also worked in a nursery. This layout is a little odd, yet it's functional. It seemed the real estate was portioned by vendor. And then the checkout was a circular building in the middle of the forest. A lot of the cacti and succulents, native plants, bedding and landscape plants, and some of the pottery were priced competitively with their corporate big box counterparts and the majority were of much better quality. However, that cannot be said with the overinflated price tags of house plant land and some of those poor things needed some water or they were so root bound from hanging out so long that they were begging to be reduced in price so that someone would take them home and repot them into something bigger. I only saw one employee working, first I saw him outside unloading pallets of freight, then he went into the cashier circle to wait on me.

I'm not sure this location was the best choice. Convenient spot, but seems to be too small. This place gets overcrowded and the lines are often long. I've ordered to go every time but once so far. The service has always been exceptional and friendly, and also quite quick for how busy it is (once you have ordered).

categories: Seafood, Bars, Wine Bars, American (New), Restaurants, French, Nightlife, Mexican
text:
We went here on a whim for desert. I had seen their menu beforehand and couldn't stop thinking about the warm Santa Barbara chocolate lava cake with Brazilian ice cream. Wow.. aren't you salivating yet? We didn't have reservations so we called to see if we could still get a table for dessert. The waitress said there were absolutely no tables and hung up on us. Rude. Despite the unfriendly first encounter, we were still enamored by the thought of the dessert. We decided to take a chance and walk over there. We got there around 9:30 pm on a Saturday and were immediately seated! There were actually a few tables open! 

The service inside was very good. Even though we just went for dessert, I had a taste of their warm bread.  Oooh, so warm, soft and not overly chewy. I have to say this is one of the best "table" breads I have ever had! 

Of course we got what we wanted: the warm chocolate cake. We split it between two of us..and it was plenty considering how rich it was. The cake was perfectly baked so the center came oozing out with melted chocolate. The ice cream was from McConnell's which is supposedly the best ice cream in town and beyond. It had the perfect amount of coffee flavor; not too strong and overbearing.. a perfect accent to the cake. I can't say this is the best lava cake I've had but it was pretty good.

name: Hotel Santa Barbara
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '3', 'WiFi': "u'free'"}
categories: Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services, Hotels
text:
Mixed feelings re: this hotel.

Positives: 

great location - you can walk to food, shopping, beach, etc.

nice extras - nice free breakfast in the morning and free tea in the afternoon and free coffee in the evening.  the breakfast pastries are not great, but hey, it's free.  the waffle maker is a plus.

Negatives:

very noisy - we were in a room perpendicular to state street but it was SO loud we could hear everything.  and the noise did not stop until around 2am each night.  if you're looking for a relaxing hotel, this is not it.  it's great if you want to be part of the drinking/partying action.  even with ear plugs in, I could hear the drumming and music from the street.

small rooms - we got the standard queen bed and it was a very very small room.  just enough space for the bed and table.  very small for $189/night on the weekend.  but perhaps that's the going rate in SB.

potentially not clean rooms- this is one of the reason's I'm giving this place a 2.  I noticed that each night I was there, I'd wake up with really red eyes, which would go away when I left the room during they day, but would inevitably reappear after spending a night in the room.  I'm certain I'm allergic to something in the room.  I asked the front desk if they had pets or smoking in the room in the past, or if they don't clean their comforters for each guest.  They told me no pets, no smoking, and that the comforter was cleaned before we got the room.  They didn't offer to do anything about it.  Perhaps it is true, but I know I've never had an allergic reaction to any other hotels I've stayed at, and the worn quality of the comforter made me question its cleanliness (worrying if I'm reacting to dust mites, etc.).  This is not a complaint against the cleaning ladies - they did a great job cleaning the place every day.  Just a little irritated with the lack of attention received from the front desk regarding this complaint (i.e., they did nothing).  Also surprised that the hotel doesn't provide lotion in the bathrooms.  Perhaps I've been too pampered at other hotels, but I just expect hotels to make you feel comfortable, rather than concerned about its potential lack of cleanliness.

So overall, location is a 5, but noise, small rooms, and lack of cleanliness brought it down to a 3.  and lack of care from the front desk re: my complaint bring it down to a 2.

categories: Restaurants, Mexican
text: Have been meaning to eat here for years and finally did. Have to say, it was a huge disappointment. Why? The food (chiles rellenos plate and shrimp caldo) was just average, and yet each dish cost $14.99! The shrimp were small and lackluster, the chiles greasy and bland. The beans and rice were afterthoughts. The atmosphere? Outdoor tables next to sidewalk and Milpas traffic. I mean, all of that is fine and acceptable for casual order at counter food, but the prices don't reflect that. For the cost, I'd expect really delicious and carefully prepared food and better setting and service. Service was just, whatever, without a smile or warmth from both the cashier and the cook who brought out food. I would never return. Instead, I'd go to Lito's, Los Agaves, Cuernavaca, even La Super Rica for goodness sake.

text:
Went here for lunch on the weekend.  Walked in and was immediately  seated in their little courtyard, which boarders State Street for a view of people walking by.  The servers were attentive, and the menu was extensive.  The food was very good and very Italian in its presentation.
Average prices are around $18.00 for entrees.  Very nice relaxing place to eat.  I would eat here again.  Great for people watching also!

name: Mission Santa Barbara
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'DogsAllowed': 'True', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False'}
categories: Churches, Arts & Entertainment, Museums, Religious Organizations, Landmarks & Historical Buildings, Public Services & Government
text: Great place to visit while you are in Santa Barbara. The mission is so beautiful and would recommend staying for at least 2 hours. There is a cost to enter the inside portion of the mission. However, the outside grounds can also be enjoyed and it is truly beautiful. Recommend wearing comfortable shoes so you can easily walk around. A lot of open area and a few picnic tables in case you want to grab some lunch before touring the grounds. Bathrooms are located outside as well. Will definitely come back the next time I am in town.
